ns2:PrimaryTypeDefinition.ns1:desc: This managed object represents the handover relationship between two neighboring EUTRAN cells.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The number of successful intra LTE intra frequency handover preparations.
The number of attempts to start intra LTE intra frequency handover preparation.
The number of successful intra LTE intra frequency handovers.
The number of intra LTE intra frequency handover execution attempts.
The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Offset value for the neighbor cell. Used when UE is in connected mode. This attribute can be modified by SON functions.
Reference to an instance of EUtranCellFDD, ExternalEUtranCellFDD, EUtranCellTDD or ExternalEUtranCellTDD managed object.
Specifies if handover between the cells in this relation is allowed.
Offset value applied to a specific cell in idle mode mobility state.

Indicates if the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function is allowed to remove this object. It does not restrict operator removal of the object. Objects created by ANR have this parameter set to true initially.

Indicates if the referred cell is included in System Information.
When the attribute is set to false, the cell is not included in either freqNeighList or blackCellList in SIB4 or SIB5.

Indicates whether the coverage area of the cell indicated by the relation has approximately the same coverage area (overlap) as this cell, or whether it fully covers this cell, or if it is fully contained in this cell.
The number of outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover execution attempts.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handovers.
The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparation.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparations.
Indicates whether the MO has been created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2
Indicates the time and date when the MO was created . Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS
Indicates whether the MO was last modified by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2 and if the MO is to be deleted who triggered the deletion
Indicates the time and date when the MO was last modified. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS
Counter pmHoOscIntraF counts every intra-frequency HO that is considered to be an oscillating HO. pmHoOscIntraF is incremented when handover preparation is attempted.
Counter pmHoOscInterF counts every inter-frequency HO that is considered to be an oscillating HO. pmHoOscInterF is incremented when handover preparation is attempted.
Counts every detected event of too early HO on an intra frequency relation.
Counts every detected event of too early HO on an inter frequency relation.
Counts every detected event of too late HO on an intra frequency relation.
Counts every detected event of too late HO on an inter frequency relation.
Counts every detected event of HO to the wrong cell on an intra frequency relation, when this neighbor cell is the attempted target cell.
Counts every detected event of HO to the wrong cell on an inter frequency relation, when this neighbor cell is the attempted target cell.
Counts every detected event of HO to the wrong cell on an intra frequency relation, when this neighbor cell is where the UE reestablished connection after the failed HO.
Counts every detected event of HO to the wrong cell on an inter frequency relation, when this neighbor cell is where the UE reestablished connection after the failed HO.
Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.

This attribute indicates whether Inter-Frequency Load Balancing is ALLOWED or NOT_ALLOWED or if Inter-Frequency Offload shall be applied from the current cell to the cell indicated by the cell relation.
Records the number of received UE measurement reports that fulfill both RSRP and RSRQ requirements. This is a subcounter of pmLbMeasRepUe.
The number of outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover execution attempts due to load balancing.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handovers that was performed for load balancing reasons.
The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparation due to load balancing.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparations that was performed for load balancing reasons.

SCell candidate status.
The value indicates whether the cell indicated by parameter cellrelation can be used as SCell for UEs using this cell as their PCell. The SCell can be either local to the eNodeB, or on a remote eNodeB.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:takesEffect: Changed value will take effect in relation to the next SCell configuration during the ongoing connection.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The number of intra LTE intra frequency handover execution attempts made by Tune-out UEs
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE intra frequency handovers made by Tune-out UEs.
Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.

The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparation due to MBMS Interest.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparations that was performed due to MBMS Interest.
The number of outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover execution attempts due to MBMS Interest.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handovers that was performed due to MBMS Interest.
Specifies if the feature Best Neighbor Relations for Intra-LTE Load Management is allowed to automatically change the loadBalancing attribute for this EUtran cell relation.

Determines if feature Overlaid Cell Detection has qualified this cell relation as an overlaid neighbor, i.e. high-hitRate, on the corresponding frequency relation.
The value "true" means the neighbor cell is encouraged to initiate load balancing towards the source cell. The value "false" means no specific preferences exist.
Determines if the cell relation has high hitRate towards the source cell. The attribute is automatically updated when the feature Overlaid Cell Detection is operable.

Records the number of attempted inter-frequency handover preparations towards the related cell, due to CA triggered redirection performed during Initial UE connection setup, when the feature CA-aware IFLB is used.

Records the number of successful inter-frequency handover preparations towards the related cell, attempted due to CA Triggered Redirection performed during Initial UE connection setup, when the feature CA-aware IFLB is used.

Records the number of attempted inter-frequency handover executions towards the related cell, due to CA Triggered Redirection performed during Initial UE connection setup, when the feature CA-aware IFLB is used.

Records the number of successful inter-frequency handover executions towards the related cell, attempted due to CA Triggered Redirection performed during Initial UE connection setup, when the feature CA-aware IFLB is used.
Records the number of received UE measurement reports that fulfill both RSRP and RSRQ requirements in connection with CA-triggered redirection, when feature CA-Aware IFLB is used.

The number of UEs that report the related LTE cell as the cell with the best RSRP value in connection with measurements initiated by Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-frequency Handover. Used to calculate the SPIFHO measurement success rate for the related cell.
The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter-frequency handover preparation due to feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-frequency Handover.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter-frequency handover preparations due to feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-frequency Handover.
The number of attempted inter-frequency handover executions towards the related cell, due to feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-frequency Handover.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter-frequency handovers that were performed due to feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-frequency Handover.
The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE handover preparation due to non-mobility reasons.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE handover preparations due to non-mobility reasons.
The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE handover executions towards the related cell due to non-mobility.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE handovers that were performed due to non-mobility reasons.
Number of UEs that are candidates for throughput based load balancing.
Number of UEs that are accepted for throughput based load balancing.
Number of received UE measurement reports in connection with Admission-Triggered Offload that fulfill both RSRP and RSRQ requirements. This is a subcounter of pmAtoMeasRepUe.
Number of out-going intra-LTE, inter-frequency handover execution attempts for QCI1 ERAB.
Number of successful out-going intra LTE inter frequency handover execution for QCI1 ERAB.

Sleep Mode Coverage Cell candidate status.
Indicates if related cell can be used as coverage cell for Cell Sleep Mode.
Indicates if related cell is a dependent capacity cell for Cell Sleep Mode support.
Indicates if related cell is a coverage cell for Cell Sleep Mode support.
DL PRB usage percentage threshold. At least one of the coverage cells must exceed this threshold to wake-up the capacity cell.
Minimum number of RRC connections needed to wake-up the capacity cell. Sent by the capacity cell.
Minimum duration for coverage cell to satisfy configured load thresholds before the capacity cell can wake-up. Used in feature Cell Sleep Mode.

Priority of neighbor cell whose CRS Assistance Information is sent to UE. For values between 1 and 100, the smaller the value, the higher the neighbor cell is prioritized for selection. Value 0 means the CRS Assistance Information of this neighbor cell is not sent. Note: This attribute is valid only for FDD cells.
Number of UEs that report the related EUTRAN cell as the strongest cell in connection with measurements initiated for Admission-Triggered Offload.
Number of UEs that report the related EUTRAN cell as the strongest cell in connection with measurements initiated for load balancing or offload.
Number of UEs that report the related EUTRAN cell as the strongest cell in connection with CA-triggered redirection, when feature CA-Aware IFLB is used.

Contains mobility status information. When struct member mobilityStatus.available is set to FALSE, no handover is performed on the cell relation. mobilityStatus.reason indicates the reason why handover is not allowed on the cell relation.
Handover statistics status information. Each value corresponds to the status of the handover statistics.

Number of attempts to start outgoing intra-LTE inter-frequency handover preparation, triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

Number of successful outgoing intra-LTE inter-frequency handover preparations, triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.
Number of UEs that are accepted for throughput based load balancing and accepted in UL evaluation.

If indicated cell is currently able to serve as ESCell. - The ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellState (or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellState) must be operState ENABLED. - Inter-eNodeB CA license must be active and baseband-to-baseband GTPU tunnel connection between ESCell and this eNodeB must be enabled. Or - Elastic RAN license must be active and baseband-to-baseband connections must be enabled. If not, no UEs are configured with this candidate. NOTE: UEs already configured with this cell can retain the configuration. If SCell is not external, this attribute is NOT_APPLICABLE.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Depends on feature license and success of tunnels in TermPointToLbm (for the IeNB-CA feature only), TermPointToENB::interEnbSwCompatibilityState and on ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellState (or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellState).

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Number of attempted handover preperations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency, - triggered by handover preparation failure from target CSG or Hybrid CSG cell.
Number of successful handover preperations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - triggered by handover preparation failure from target CSG or Hybrid CSG cell.
Number of attempted handover executions that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - triggered by handover preparation failure from target CSG or Hybrid CSG cell.
Number of successful handovers that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - triggered by handover preparation failure from target CSG or Hybrid CSG cell.
Whether or not AMO function is allowed. Used to turn off AMO function on cell relation level.
Describes AMO function enabling state. RBS system sets the value.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Depends on the operator configuration of AmoFunction::amoAllowedInterVendor, EUtranFreqRelation::amoAllowed, EUtranCellRelation::amoAllowed and the type of cell relation.
